    "updated_at": "2025-06-17T02:41:39Z",
    "body": "# Comparison of the performance metrics for powerlevel10k and starship\n\n| Metric                  | p10k     | starship |\n|-------------------------|----------|----------|\n| creates_tty             | 0        | 0        |\n| has_compsys             | 1        | 1        |\n| has_syntax_highlighting | 1        | 1        |\n| has_autosuggestions     | 1        | 1        |\n| has_git_prompt          | 1        | 1        |\n| first_prompt_lag_ms     | 21.287   | 106.149  |\n| first_command_lag_ms    | 146.342  | 136.635  |\n| command_lag_ms          | 14.064   | 32.221   |\n| input_lag_ms            | 13.621   | 11.157   |\n| exit_time_ms            | 65.351   | 64.840   |\n\nAs shown above, there are noticeable performance differences between powerlevel10k and starship:\n\n- **First prompt lag**[^1]: p10k is about 5 times faster\n- **Command lag**[^2]: p10k is about 2 times faster\n\n[^1]: Time from starting the shell to when the prompt appears on screen.\n[^2]: Time from pressing Enter on an empty command line to when the next prompt appears.\n",
    "author_association": "NONE",
